.TH "i3c_master_disec_locked" 9 "i3c_master_disec_locked" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i3c_master_disec_locked \- send a DISEC CCC command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i3c_master_disec_locked
.BI "(struct i3c_master_controller *master "  ","
.BI "u8 addr "  ","
.BI "u8 evts "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "master" 12
master used to send frames on the bus
.IP "addr" 12
a valid I3C slave address or I3C_BROADCAST_ADDR
.IP "evts" 12
events to disable
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Send a DISEC CCC command to disable some or all events coming from a
specific slave, or all devices if \fIaddr\fP is I3C_BROADCAST_ADDR.

This function must be called with the bus lock held in write mode.
.SH "RETURN"
0 in case of success, a positive I3C error code if the error is
one of the official Mx error codes, and a negative error code otherwise.
